The RequestContext object facilitates requests to the Visio application. Since the Office add-in and the Visio application run in two different processes, the request context is required to get access to the Visio object model from the add-in.

run.signature: export function run<T>(objects: OfficeExtension.ClientObject[], batch: (context: Visio.RequestContext) => Promise<T>): Promise<T>;

description.text: An array of previously-created API objects. The array will be validated to make sure that all of the objects share the same context. The batch will use this shared request context, which means that any changes applied to these objects will be picked up by "context.sync()".
